description: This top floor apartment is in the stunning Lakefront complex and yes it is on an island! Not only will you love the fact that you live on an island, but you will also have a home on a cul de sac, and who would have thought that possible in this buzzy inner south precinct?This property is something different thanks to this wonderful location. You will have more privacy, less noise, better street parking and quicker access to the Lake Foreshore than just about any other complex not on it's own island!  My owner certainly thinks so, it's why she bought here in the first place! Sadly, circumstances decree that we must sell, and soon.  Not only do you get to live on an Island but you pretty much get to live in a penthouse too! Top floor, so no neighbours above, and only one other on your floor. From number 46 you look down onto the sparkling infinity pool, you can hear the cows grazing on the dairy flats, enjoy stunning sunsets behind the Carillion from your large balcony not to mention foreshore vistas from both bedrooms. All of this can be yours.I am assured that the balcony is so private you can confidently avoid any kind of tan line if you so desire! The living area and balcony face North East so the sun pours into your living room and means you have a terrace that you and your plants can bask on for most of the day.This elegant apartment has wrap around windows in the open plan living area, so you get fabulous views designed to be enjoyed from the luxury of your sofa. The kitchen has a fantastic work area with granite island and good storage. The balcony accommodates a BBQ, generous table an AND those important sunloungers, so the whole space is fabulous for entertaining.The cool bathroom interiors are simple, and sleek and the ensuite is generous with double sink and a good sized shower. The main bedroom has it's own private balcony which is the perfect place to snooze in the shade of a summer afternoon. Other impressive features are the wonderfully practical garbage chute (no bins for you!) and the two car parks are right next door to the lift that takes you to your front door..This is such a great opportunity if you are downsizing, or a busy executive or want to invest now and move in later. The Foreshore offers such easy living, with local restaurants offering great mid week specials you won't be bothered to cook half the time! The atmosphere on the Foreshore is communal and fun..with the iconic Bus Depot and Glassworks on your doorstep.We are selling, so you should not delay in getting down to see us.

description: Offering a massive 600sqm of build area this custom designed home has been intelligently designed with all the bedrooms upstairs, leaving the downstairs dedicated to family living and entertaining. It is perfectly situated on a large 745sqm block with your very own resort out the back, which includes an outdoor kitchen and a sparkling below ground pool. When everyone wants their own favourite space, this massive home delivers! This magnificent residence was built by the award winning Residential Attitudes and offers glorious sea views (some never to be built out). It is perfect for modern families who need a large, family-friendly home with plenty of entertaining options both inside and out.The property is brilliantly situated in an outstanding Quinns Beach Estate location just a 30 second walk to the coastal cycling and walking tracks. A friendly neighbourhood with an unrivalled laid back coastal lifestyle. With the beach, dog beach and beachside cafes all being close by, you will feel like you are on holiday all the time. The area boasts many amenities including schools, shops, medical centre and restaurants.This gigantic property consists of 4 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms, 2 powder rooms, study/home office, formal lounge and dining, open plan kitchen, dining and living, games room (with bar),  alfresco, home theatre, activity, laundry, balcony and an extra large double garage.  The striking front elevation of the home with feature stone work gives an early indication of the amazing property that lies within. DownstairsA stunning entry foyer welcomes you in to the home and sets the tone for the abundance of space and light on offer. You could literally hold a dance party just in the entry!. To the left you step down to the enormous formal lounge and dining spaces with their gorgeous bulkhead ceilings and designer lighting. The large study/home office could also be used as a 5th bedroom. It features a triple wardrobe and has direct access to the terrace at the front of the home.Through double doors at the end of the entry foyer the travertine floor flows through in to the spacious open plan kitchen, dining and living areas. The superbly appointed kitchen anchors this space and is a focal point for the family to meet up and entertain. The kitchen features stunning 40mm Qstone seashell stone benchtops (waterfall edges) and backsplash. Other features are 900mm stainless steel oven, cooktop and rangehood, stainless steel dishwasher, microwave recess, fridge/freezer recess,  walk in pantry and lot's of bench and cupboard space.  A ceiling bulkhead provides the perfect finishing touch to the gorgeous kitchen area. The kitchen overlooks the family area which features a large welcoming wall mounted electric wood fireplace. Adjacent is the dining area which has great views over the pool. Stacker doors open up from the dining area in to the alfresco. You have your very own luxury escape in the back garden. It features a stunning, sparkling below ground concrete pool plus a separate kids paddling pool. Glass pool fencing, liquid limestone floors and a grassed area perfect for kids and pets are other features. The alfresco is a great place for outdoor dining with it's built in BBQ (gas connection) and sink. Back inside, just when you thought there could not possibly be anymore entertaining space on offer, there is large games room with built in bar. A powder room room is centrally located. There is also a well appointed laundry with lot's of cupboard and bench space. Completing the downstairs is an extra large 49sqm garage with 2.7 metre door access and a 3 metre high internal garage ceiling.UpstairsThe signature sea views and sensational Indian Ocean sunsets can be enjoyed from the balcony and master bedroom. The enormous, decadent master suite features coffered ceilings and a gorgeous ensuite with floor to ceiling tiling, double vanities, twin shower, spa bath, and a separate toilet. There is also a huge fitted walk in wardrobe.The other 3 bedrooms are all king size with double built in wardrobes. A beautiful family bathroom features double vanities a shower and a bath as well as a separate powder room.The luxurious gold class home theatre is on a grand scale, just like the rest of the home.  With tiered seating, coffered ceilings and featured downlights, you can't get any closer to a true cinema experience.A further lounge/sitting space flows out through sliding doors to the large balcony where you can enjoy your favourite drink while watching another beautiful sunset. Other features of this amazing property are:- Daikon zoned ducted reverse cycle air conditioning.- Valet ducted vacuum system. - Security alarm system.- Automated reticulation controllable by mobile phone app.- Intelligent home smart wiring to data.- Clipsail Saturn neon light switches throughout.- Designer lighting.- 32 course high ceilings.Plus so much more!.Property Measurements:Ground FloorAlfresco                  36.78sqmGarage                   49.52sqmGround Floor         247.09sqmTerrace                    22.68sqmUpper FloorBalcony                   31.47sqmUpper Floor          213.86sqmTotal Home           601.40sqmViewings are by appointment only, so don't delay as properties of this size and quality, in this prime location rarely come on the market. description: With a fresh look inside and out, a low maintenance layout and easy-care yard, there will be plenty of time to enjoy this East Maitland property's perfect positioning.Located less than 150m from the championship 18-hole golf course and delicious a la carte dining and entertainment facilities at Easts Leisure and Golf, the property is a dream downsizer for golfing enthusiasts.It's central position also puts it just a short drive from the cafes, boutiques, galleries and antique stores on Lawes and Melbourne streets, and the bustling retail and hospitality hub of Stockland Green Hills, ensuring plenty of other options to fill your time when you're not on the fairways and greens.Ideal for those looking for less space and more leisure time, the well presented two-bedroom bench.The rendered cladding and Colorbond roof give the home modern appeal, while a new coat of paint inside and out and a modern timber and glass feature entry door freshens up its finish.An open plan design in the lounge, dining and kitchen creates a seamless flow between the adjoining rooms, while tiled flooring adds to the natural connectivity of the living spaces.While a light, neutral colour palette has been used on the walls to enhance the bright and airy ambience, the darker timber of the architraves and skirting boards and the bright golden tones of the country-style timber kitchen add warmth and textures to the rooms.Overhead and underbench cabinetry and a separate pantry ensure the cosy kitchen has plenty of storage space, while timber and laminate return benchtops and a breakfast bar offer ample preparation areas as well as a space for casual meals.Sliding glass doors open the dining room up to the adjoining covered alfresco area, making entertaining friends and family easy all year round, while double side gates also provide access to this space from the front yard.A reverse cycle split system air conditioner in the dining room provides climate controlled comfort at the heart of the home, while ceiling fans in the bedrooms and lounge room help keep these areas cool in summer.The two bedrooms are both of a good size and feature built-in wardrobes as well as new carpet and new day-night roller blinds for a fresh, modern look. Both provide easy access to the nearby well-appointed bathroom and separate toilet.Perfectly positioned in the sought-after suburb of East Maitland, the property offers easy access to the growing medical precincts in surrounding areas, which include a large private hospital, a range of healthcare specialists and a new state-of-the-art regional hospital and emergency room currently under construction in the nearby suburb of Metford.Its central position also puts the best of Newcastle and the Hunter Valley within easy reach, with the tourist mecca of Morpeth and the revitalised Maitland city centre less than 10 minutes away.A 40-minute drive in opposite directions will see you enjoying the beaches and boutiques of Newcastle or sipping on a glass of wine in the world-renowned Hunter Valley vineyards, where a host of championship golf courses, fine dining restaurants and rejuvenating day spas also await.You can also relax with a whale watching cruise or enjoy the delights of Nelson Bay's D'Albora Marina in just over 50 minutes, while Sydney's wide array of attractions are just a two-hour drive down the M1 motorway.SMS 26aPat to 0428 166 755 for a link to the online property brochure.

description: "Grand and spacious with Style and Character to Match"Steeped in history and exuding unparalleled charm, this grand and spacious property must be seen to be believed. Once situated on the highest block in Strathalbyn and home of two past Strathalbyn Mayors, this lovely circa 1920s stone home offers a welcome respite to the everyday chaos of city life. The entrance of the home offers the first glimpse of the delights to follow, with a striking wrought iron door inviting access to the formal foyer and beyond. 12 foot high ceilings, dappled light, rendered archways and wide passageways are just a few of the charming features of this unique property. The main and second bedrooms are extraordinarily spacious and the third, although slightly smaller, is bright and enchanting. The living area features a slow combustion heater that warms the entire living space on those chilly winter nights, as well as a unique feature wall of arched dormer windows and a recessed feature mantle. This flows into a functional dining area, both of which are graced with bright window seat areas.  Between the kitchen and the dining areas is a heritage style butlers pantry that also houses the entrance to the underground cellar. The kitchen has been recently renovated and is expansive and bright. With a double Falcon oven and Miele dishwasher, this old stone home has been smoothly integrated into the modern era. From here you move into the Family room, which is another more recent addition to the home. There is a segregated area that functions easily as a laundry with its own access to the outdoor pergola area. The family room features double glass doors as well as a large picture window, offering light and many entertainment options. There is also another toilet hidden at the rear of this extension. The bathroom is aged, but functional, with quite a few delightful features  including unique tap ware, a deep bath, shower piping and saloon style shower doors.The expansive yard of  1757m2 is an entertainers delight, with beautifully landscaped gardens that feature a number of seating nooks and play areas for children. There is a sheltered fire pit area for those clear spring nights that simply beckon to be shared with a glass of red wine and an enclosed patio that offers an extra outdoor entertaining area from the family room at the rear of the house.  The back yard also features a double garage, garden shed, 3 enormous rain water tanks, a cubby house and sandpit, numerous established fruit trees and a vegetable garden. If this isnt enough, the garden and lawn are low maintenance, serviced by a modern watering system. Other fabulous features this unique home has to offer are its 10 kilowatt solar system, 3 phase power outlet in the rear shed, sub surface irrigation and its walking access to local shopping and schools. Although ready for its new owners to move into and live comfortably, this home also has enormous opportunity for a savvy renovator to add elements of their own personality. With only a 45-minute commute to the city, this could just be the rural retreat you have been looking for.

description: 300 Upper Brookfield Road is a trip down memory lane. Legend has it, The Hainings’s grew both Mangoes and Pawpaws and supplied the local fruit markets. The mangoes and pawpaws were transported by horse drawn slide which remains on the homestead. Keen eyes will also notice the old "Thunderbox" still remains onsite as a reminder of how local's lived back then; thankfully replaced by more modern facilities.     Comprising one of the most usable, cleared and picturesque parcels of land this stunning 8.5acres of perfect fertile grounds is flanked by a creek and offers incredible future potential. Features Include:- Fully Renovated 3 bedroom "Queenslander" - Refurbished Bathroom- High ceilings, VJ Walls, Lead light windows, new lighting, fresh paint and carpets throughout - Brand new kitchen with timber bench tops - Completely rewired and new power box fitted- New plumbing throughout including 20,000L water tank, new pump and a secondary 5,000L water tank and pumpLand Component:- 8.5 acres of prime, usable, flat land eagerly awaits its next owner with endless possibilities with a clearer building envelope, open paddocks and lush lawns.   - Large, cleared open paddocks ideal for horses, cattle, livestock and lifestyle opportunities for families- Abundance of room for a substantial home, tennis courts, pool, additional sheds or infrastructure- Orchard and bush tracks throughout- Flowing creek at the rear of the land contains beautiful clear high quality water- Superb balance of privacy, vegetation and pastoral grounds- Rural zoning- Incredible buffer from neighbouring properties- NBN internet connection available- Moments to Brookfield Village, Showgrounds, General store and local schools- Convenient to Kenmore central and access for Southern cross bus services300 Upper Brookfield Road encompasses the very essence of dream old fashioned rural lifestyle. This is one of the last remaining rural land holdings throughout the highly sought after suburb of Brookfield. Call now to arrange a private viewing to access all aspects and areas of the land.

description: Just imagine the lifestyle and gracious living offered by this fine example of elegance and true craftsmanship.Transvaal is one of those tightly held homes that grabs the heart and becomes more of a love affair, which is exactly why our vendors are only the third owners ever since the home was built in 1919.Builder Ernest Clephane was highly respected around Launceston in the late 1800's and some of his works included The Albert Hall, Duck Reach Power Station, The Majestic Theatre in Brisbane Street (now known as The Princess Theatre), National Theatre in Charles Street, The Gasworks in Cimitiere Street and the Launceston Church Grammar School.When it came time to build his own family home he really wanted to make a statement and that's exactly what he did after he designed and constructed 21 Home Street.With tuck point brick work, beautiful leadlight windows, formal dining room, soaring 12" ceilings, ornate fretwork and mantles, Transvaal takes all the hallmarks of federation period and blends it beautifully with modern day living.This home really must be seen to be appreciated.Call Harley for more information today.

The faade is deceptive and understated, however once you walk inside, this home is full of surprises.The master suite is located at the front of the property with striking jarrah flooring, old sash windows, incredibly high ceilings a decorative fireplace, walk in robes and an ensuite.The two minor bedrooms are generously proportioned with plenty enough space for a king size bed, study and toys.  The main bathroom is perfectly positioned and finished to perfection.The laundry and toilet are off set from the driveway, with ample storage options, broom cupboard, double linen cupboard and an attic.The near new extension of this property allows you to have an open plan living, dining and kitchen area with a separate theatre room which could be used as a home office or fourth bedroom.  The kitchen has plenty of bench space so you can cook up a storm and entertain at the same time. A study nook is also positioned in the kitchen for convenience. These rooms have plenty of natural night with the abundance of glass doors or windows.All overlooking the tranquil backyard with timber decked entertaining area  and a grassed area for children to play on or an additional place for you to park your vehicle.A rare incredibly spacious family home with all the modern necessities one desires.A must see to appreciate!
